{"build_type":"library","description":"Channel B unified kernel serve+lifecycle loop. Polls (event-driven, no busy-wait) over two descriptors: the portal request eventfd (fd 3) and the shutdown signalfd (sfd). When fd 3 is ready it serves one request through serve-portal-region-request-running-helper-writing-reply (passing the shell path); when the signalfd is ready it stops init (kill the supervisor pid, wait4) and returns for orderly shutdown. Tail-recursive. The gate-aware kernel-root calls this so one loop both serves portal requests and handles the power button. Additive Channel B.","module_name":"serve-portal-request-watching-shutdown-event-perpetually","package_name":"serve-portal-request-watching-shutdown-event-perpetually","function_definitions":{"serve-portal-request-watching-shutdown-event-perpetually":{"return_type":"i64","parameter_definitions":[{"parameter_name":"shell_path","parameter_type":"i64"},{"parameter_name":"sfd","parameter_type":"i64"},{"parameter_name":"initpid","parameter_type":"i64"}],"execution_instructions":[{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"zero","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":0},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"one","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":1},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"two","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":2},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"three","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":3},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"four","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":4},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"six","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":6},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"eight","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operatio